ApplyConcurrent.document: This API is used to request concurrency quota. The timeout period of the API is 20 seconds.
ApplyConcurrent.name: Requests concurrency quota

BindConcurrentPackagesToProject.document: This API is used to bind a concurrency pack to a project.
BindConcurrentPackagesToProject.name: Binds a concurrency pack to a project

CreateApplication.document: This API is used to create an application.
CreateApplication.name: Creates a cloud application

CreateApplicationProject.document: This API is used to create a cloud application project.
CreateApplicationProject.name: Creates a cloud application project

CreateApplicationSnapshot.document: This API is used to create a cloud application version snapshot.
CreateApplicationSnapshot.name: Creates a cloud application snapshot

CreateApplicationVersion.document: This API is used to create a cloud application version.
CreateApplicationVersion.name: Creates a cloud application version

CreateSession.document: This API is used to create a session. The timeout period of the API is 5 seconds.
CreateSession.name: Creates a session

DeleteApplication.document: This API is used to delete a cloud application.
DeleteApplication.name: Deletes a cloud application

DeleteApplicationProjects.document: This API is used to delete cloud application projects in batches.
DeleteApplicationProjects.name: Deletes cloud application projects in batches

DeleteApplicationVersion.document: This API is used to delete a cloud application version.
DeleteApplicationVersion.name: Deletes a cloud application version

DescribeApplicationFileInfo.document: This API is used to query application file information.
DescribeApplicationFileInfo.name: Queries application file information

DescribeApplicationList.document: This API is used to query the cloud application list.
DescribeApplicationList.name: Queries the cloud application list

DescribeApplicationPathList.document: This API is used to query the cloud application startup path list.
DescribeApplicationPathList.name: Queries the cloud application startup path list

DescribeApplicationProjectAdvancedConfig.document: This API is used to obtain the advanced configuration information of a cloud application project.
DescribeApplicationProjectAdvancedConfig.name: Obtains the configuration information of a cloud application project

DescribeApplicationProjects.document: This API is used to obtain the cloud application project list.
DescribeApplicationProjects.name: Obtains the cloud application project list

DescribeApplicationStatus.document: This API is used to query the running status of a cloud application and update status information.
DescribeApplicationStatus.name: Queries cloud application status

DescribeApplicationVersion.document: This API is used to query the version information of a cloud application.
DescribeApplicationVersion.name: Queries the version information of a cloud application

DescribeConcurrentCount.document: This API is used to obtain the concurrency count.
DescribeConcurrentCount.name: Obtains the concurrency count

DescribeConcurrentPackages.document: This API is used to obtain the cloud application concurrency pack list.
DescribeConcurrentPackages.name: Obtains the cloud application concurrency pack list

DescribeConcurrentSummary.document: This API is used to query the concurrency overview.
DescribeConcurrentSummary.name: Queries the concurrency overview

DescribeCosCredential.document: This API is used to query COS key information.
DescribeCosCredential.name: Queries COS key information

DestroySession.document: This API is used to terminate a session. If cloud-based streaming has been enabled for this session, the cloud-based streaming will end upon session termination.
DestroySession.name: Terminates a session

ModifyApplicationBaseInfo.document: This API is used to modify basic information of a cloud application.
ModifyApplicationBaseInfo.name: Modifies basic information of a cloud application

ModifyApplicationProject.document: This API is used to modify a cloud application project.
ModifyApplicationProject.name: Modifies a cloud application project

ModifyApplicationVersion.document: This API is used to modify the version information of a cloud application.
ModifyApplicationVersion.name: Modifies the version information of a cloud application

ModifyConcurrentPackage.document: This API is used to modify a cloud application concurrency pack.
ModifyConcurrentPackage.name: Modifies a cloud application concurrency pack

ModifyMobileApplicationInfo.document: This API is used to modify the mobile application data.
ModifyMobileApplicationInfo.name: Modifies the mobile application information

ResetConcurrentPackages.document: This API is used to reset a concurrency pack and disconnect all user connections.
ResetConcurrentPackages.name: Resets a concurrency pack

SetApplicationVersionOnline.document: This API is used to launch an application version.
SetApplicationVersionOnline.name: Launches a cloud application version

StartPublishStream.document: This API is used to start pushing your cloud application's video streams in real time to CSS. The codec for the streaming is automatically selected based on the client's (SDK) capabilities, with a default order of H.265, H.264, VP8, and VP9.
StartPublishStream.name: Starts pushing streams

StartPublishStreamWithURL.document: This API is used to start pushing your cloud application's video streams to a specified URL. The codec for the streaming is automatically selected based on the client's (SDK) capabilities, with a default order of H.265, H.264, VP8, and VP9. This streaming method will be billed separately. For details about the billing method, see [Charging for Streaming to Specified URL](https://intl.cloud.tencent.com/document/product/1547/72168?from_cn_redirect=1#98ac188a-d122-4caf-88be-05268ecefdf6).
StartPublishStreamWithURL.name: Starts pushing streams to a specified URL

StopPublishStream.document: This API is used to stop pushing streams.
StopPublishStream.name: Stops pushing streams

UnbindConcurrentPackagesFromProject.document: This API is used to unbind a concurrency pack from a project.
UnbindConcurrentPackagesFromProject.name: Unbinds a concurrency pack from a project

members.document:
Application startup parameters.This parameter is effective for multi-application projects.
This parameter is effective for single-application projects with prelaunch disabled.This parameter is ineffective for single-application projects with prelaunch enabled.
Note: When this parameter is effective, it will be appended to the startup parameters of application or project configuration in the console.
For example, for a single-application project with prelaunch disabled, if its startup parameter `bar` is `0` for project configuration in the console and the `ApplicationParameters` parameter `foo` is `1`, the actual application startup parameters will be `bar=0 and foo=1`.
members.name: ApplicationParameters
